<p>Search for the required items by using the filters.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Enter the quantity of the item you want to add to the order.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Add the items to the order by clicking on the shopping cart (<span class="icon darkGrey"><i class="fa fa-shopping-cart  "></i></span>) at the end of the row.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Repeat these steps to add further items.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>When all items are added, go to the next step by clicking on <strong>Overview</strong>.<br>
→ The shopping cart is saved.</p>
</li>
</ol>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>The number of items added is displayed on the shopping cart icon (<span class="icon darkGrey"><i class="fa fa-shopping-cart  "></i></span>) which is located above the table. If you want to check or delete the added items, open this shopping cart (<span class="icon darkGrey"><i class="fa fa-shopping-cart  "></i></span>).</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph subhead">
<p>Shopping cart</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>The added items are displayed in the shopping cart. You can edit the <strong>quantity</strong> as well as the <strong>price</strong>. If a price is entered that is lower than the purchase price, an error message is displayed. You can still set this lower price if you want to.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>You can also delete items in the shopping cart. To do so, click on <strong>Delete</strong> (<span class="icon red"><i class="fa fa-minus-circle  "></i></span>).</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>After you added all the items in the required quantity and with the right prices to the shopping cart, click on <strong>Overview</strong>. You could also go back to the order details by clicking on <strong>Order details</strong>. <em>But note</em> that all shopping cart data is lost when you go back.</p>
</div>
</div>
<div class="sect3">
<h4 id="290">2.4.5. Overview: Completing the order</h4>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>In this last step, the order is completed. The <strong>Total amount gross</strong> and <strong>Total amount net</strong> of the order are displayed above the order details. Also displayed are the number of order items.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>In the order details, the <strong>Shopping method</strong> and the <strong>Shopping costs</strong> can be adapted if required. Apart from the addresses, the currency and the warehouse setting, the order details are editable.</p>
</div>
<div class="paragraph">
<p>Below the order details, a table with the added order items is displayed. In addition to the information given in the previous adding items view, the prices and the VAT rate are shown. The prices can be edited as long as the order is not completed. The VAT rates are editable if you allowed this in the <a href="/en/orders/managing-orders#250">default settings</a>.</p>
</div>
<div class="openblock collapseBox">
<div class="title"><strong>Customise table</strong></div>
<div class="content">
<div class="paragraph">
<p>The table in the last step of the order create is customisable. This means that you can decide which table columns are displayed in which order. The following table columns are selected by default when you go to the purchase order menu:</p>
</div>
<div class="ulist">
<ul>
<li>
<p>Item ID/Variation ID</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Variation no.</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Description</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Attributes</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Variation name</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Purchase price</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Net price</p>
</li>
<li>
<p>Gross price</p>
</li>
